Step 2 — Extract Facts (LLM call)

Prompt:

Extract only verifiable factual claims. No opinions.

Output:

[
  {"fact": "Fed raised rates by 0.25%", "confidence": 0.95},
  {"fact": "Vote was 7-2", "confidence": 0.9}
]


⸻

Step 3 — Merge Facts

Deduplicate manually or via similarity:

unique_facts = list(set(facts))


⸻

Step 4 — Define 3 Bias Profiles

Hardcode them:

profiles = [
  {"name": "neutral"},
  {"name": "economic"},
  {"name": "human_impact"}
]


⸻

Step 5 — Generate 3 Summaries

Prompt:

Using ONLY these facts, generate a summary from the perspective of [PROFILE]. Do not invent facts.

